  <h2 style="color:#ffcc00;">Combining CSS Animations with JavaScript üé®‚ö°</h2>
  <p>CSS animations add life to web pages, while JavaScript allows you to control and trigger animations dynamically. Let‚Äôs explore how to combine them!</p>

  <h3 style="color:#ffcc00;">1. Why Combine CSS + JS? ü§î</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Dynamic Control:</strong> Start, stop, or modify animations based on user interactions.</li>
    <li><strong>Enhanced Interactivity:</strong> Trigger effects on clicks, hovers, scrolls.</li>
    <li><strong>Flexibility:</strong> Change animation properties dynamically without rewriting CSS.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 style="color:#ffcc00;">2. CSS Animation Basics üé•</h3>
  <p>Key properties:</p>
  <code>
@keyframes fadeIn {<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;0% { opacity: 0; }<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;100% { opacity: 1; }<br>
}<br><br>
.box {<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;animation-name: fadeIn;<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;animation-duration: 2s;<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;animation-timing-function: ease-in;<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;animation-delay: 0s;<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;animation-iteration-count: 1;<br>
}
  </code>

  <h3 style="color:#ffcc00;">3. Adding Interactivity with JavaScript üñ±Ô∏è</h3>
  <p>You can add or remove CSS classes dynamically to trigger animations.</p>

  <p><strong>Example: Button Click to Animate a Box</strong></p>
  <button id="animateBtn" style="background:#ffcc00;color:#680202;padding:6px 10px;border:none;border-radius:5px;cursor:pointer;">Animate Box</button>
  <div id="box" class="box" style="width:100px;height:100px;background:#3498db;margin:15px 0;opacity:0;transition:opacity 0.3s;"></div>

  <code>
.box.animate {<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;opacity: 1;<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;animation: moveRight 2s ease-in-out forwards;<br>
}<br><br>
@keyframes moveRight {<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;0% { transform: translateX(0); }<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;100% { transform: translateX(200px); }<br>
}
  </code>

  <script>
    document.getElementById("animateBtn").addEventListener("click", function () {
      const box = document.getElementById("box");
      box.classList.toggle("animate");
    });
  </script>

  <h3 style="color:#ffcc00;">4. Using Inline Styles for More Control</h3>
  <p>JavaScript can directly modify CSS properties.</p>

  <p><strong>Example: Dynamic Animation Duration</strong></p>
  <button id="startAnimation" style="background:#ffcc00;color:#680202;padding:6px 10px;border:none;border-radius:5px;cursor:pointer;">Start Animation</button>
  <div id="circle" style="width:50px;height:50px;background:#e74c3c;border-radius:50%;margin:15px 0;position:relative;"></div>

  <script>
    document.getElementById("startAnimation").addEventListener("click", function () {
      const circle = document.getElementById("circle");
      circle.style.animation = "expand 3s ease-in-out forwards";
    });

    const styleSheet = document.styleSheets[0];
    styleSheet.insertRule(`
      @keyframes expand {
        0% { transform: scale(1); }
        100% { transform: scale(2); }
      }
    `, styleSheet.cssRules.length);
  </script>

  <h3 style="color:#ffcc00;">5. Controlling Animations with Events üöÄ</h3>
  <p>Start, pause, and resume animations dynamically:</p>

  <button id="pause" style="background:#ffcc00;color:#680202;padding:6px 10px;border:none;border-radius:5px;cursor:pointer;">Pause</button>
  <button id="resume" style="background:#ffcc00;color:#680202;padding:6px 10px;border:none;border-radius:5px;cursor:pointer;">Resume</button>
  <div id="movingBox" style="width:100px;height:100px;background:#8e44ad;margin:15px 0;animation:slide 5s linear infinite;"></div>

  <style>
    @keyframes slide { 0% { transform: translateX(0); } 100% { transform: translateX(300px); } }
  </style>

  <script>
    const box = document.getElementById("movingBox");
    document.getElementById("pause").addEventListener("click", () => box.style.animationPlayState = "paused");
    document.getElementById("resume").addEventListener("click", () => box.style.animationPlayState = "running");
  </script>

  <h3 style="color:#ffcc00;">6. Example: Interactive Modal</h3>
  <button id="openModal" style="background:#ffcc00;color:#680202;padding:6px 10px;border:none;border-radius:5px;cursor:pointer;">Open Modal</button>
  <div id="modal" class="modal" style="display:none;position:fixed;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;background:rgba(0,0,0,0.5);justify-content:center;align-items:center;">
    <div class="modal-content" style="background:#fff;color:#000;padding:20px;border-radius:10px;animation:scaleUp 0.5s ease forwards;">
      <span id="closeModal" class="close" style="cursor:pointer;font-weight:bold;">&times;</span>
      <p>Modal Content Here!</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <style>
    @keyframes scaleUp { 0% { transform: scale(0); opacity: 0; } 100% { transform: scale(1); opacity:1; } }
  </style>

  <script>
    const modal = document.getElementById("modal");
    document.getElementById("openModal").addEventListener("click", () => modal.classList.add("show"));
    document.getElementById("closeModal").addEventListener("click", () => modal.classList.remove("show"));
    const style = document.createElement('style');
    style.innerHTML = `.modal.show { display:flex; }`;
    document.head.appendChild(style);
  </script>

  <h3 style="color:#ffcc00;">7. Tips & Tools üõ†Ô∏è</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Tools:</strong> GSAP (GreenSock) for complex animations, Lottie for JSON-based animations.</li>
    <li>Use CSS for simple hover effects, JS for logic-driven animations.</li>
    <li>Optimize performance using <code>transform</code> and <code>opacity</code> instead of <code>width</code> or <code>height</code>.</li>
  </ul>

  <p>By combining CSS animations and JavaScript, you can craft interactive, engaging websites. Experiment, test, and let your creativity shine! üöÄ‚ú®</p>

